  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education &amp; empowerment through community-run Play and Reading Schemes (Ghana)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Good quality early childhood education is an important determinant for how well a child will do later in school. In northern Ghana, the government has only recently begun to implement its policy of early childhood education for all, and the early childhood development on offer is often of poor quality. This project works with volunteer mothers - often the poorest women in communities - so they can support their children to learn through play. It will offer &#x2018;Play Schemes&#x2019; that encourage early childhood learning for those between three and five. These are followed by &#x2018;Reading Schemes&#x2019; where older children help those between five and eight to learn how to read. Everyone who takes part will also be taught basic hygiene to help promote good health. The schemes will help thousands of children do better at school, and will help make volunteers more confident and skilled.</narrative>
  </description>
